## Enroll + provision workflow
```bash
# 1) Create node
{{ ironic_cli_wrapper_path }} node create \
  --driver redfish \
  --driver-info redfish_address=<redfish https endpoint> \
  --driver-info redfish_username=<bmc user> \
  --driver-info redfish_password=<bmc password> \
  --driver-info redfish_verify_ca=False

# 2) Move to manageable
{{ ironic_cli_wrapper_path }} node manage <node id>

# 3) Attach cleaning network data
{{ ironic_cli_wrapper_path }} node set --network-data network_data.json <node id>

# 4) Move to available (runs cleaning)
{{ ironic_cli_wrapper_path }} node provide <node id>
# 5) Set deploy image (direct deploy example)
{% if ubuntu_lts_image_enabled | bool %}
# Ubuntu whole-disk image
{{ ironic_cli_wrapper_path }} node set <node id> \
  --instance-info image_type=whole-disk \
  --instance-info image_disk_format={{ ubuntu_lts_image_disk_format }} \
  --instance-info image_source={{ ubuntu_lts_image_http_url }} \
  --instance-info image_os_hash_algo=sha256 \
  --instance-info image_os_hash_value=$(curl -fsSL {{ ubuntu_lts_image_checksum_http_url }})
{% else %}
{{ ironic_cli_wrapper_path }} node set <node id> \
  --instance-info image_type=whole-disk \
  --instance-info image_disk_format=<raw|qcow2> \
  --instance-info image_source=<url to os image> \
  --instance-info image_os_hash_algo=sha256 \
  --instance-info image_os_hash_value=<os image sha256sum>
{% endif %}

# 6) Deploy
{{ ironic_cli_wrapper_path }} node deploy <node id> --config-drive <config-drive.json, optional>
```

## Flatcar direct deployment (Ignition via config-drive user_data)
This mode uses direct deploy with a mirrored whole-disk Flatcar image and passes Ignition as config-drive `user_data`.
The Flatcar image URL in these examples (`{{ flatcar_image_http_url }}`) is the local mirror generated by `os-image-downloader.service` (one-shot).
Deploy seeds a default Ignition file at `{{ flatcar_ignition_local_path }}` and serves it at `{{ flatcar_ignition_http_url }}`; replace that file when you want custom first-boot behavior.
For a quick end-to-end demo, this repository includes `server_templates/flatcar-demo.ign`, available at `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mattcburns/ironic-ansible/master/server_templates/flatcar-demo.ign` (replace `master` when testing from another ref).
```bash
# 1) Ensure direct deploy mode
{{ ironic_cli_wrapper_path }} node set <node id> --deploy-interface direct

# 2) Set Flatcar whole-disk image
{{ ironic_cli_wrapper_path }} node set <node id> \
  --instance-info image_type=whole-disk \
  --instance-info image_disk_format={{ flatcar_image_disk_format }} \
  --instance-info image_source={{ flatcar_image_http_url }} \
  --instance-info image_os_hash_algo=sha256 \
  --instance-info image_os_hash_value=$(curl -fsSL {{ flatcar_image_checksum_http_url }})

# 3) Deploy using config-drive user_data blob (server-side config-drive build)
{{ ironic_cli_wrapper_path }} node deploy <node id> --config-drive "$(
  jq -cn --rawfile ign {{ flatcar_ignition_local_path }} '{user_data:$ign}'
)"
```
The demo Ignition writes `/etc/flatcar-demo.txt` so you can validate that Ignition ran successfully.
It also creates a demo login for quick verification: username `demo`, password `demo-password` (intentionally insecure; demo use only).
